  "response": "On September 11, 2001, a series of coordinated terrorist attacks were carried out by the militant group al-Qaeda against targets in the United States. Here's a brief overview of the main events:\n\n1. **Hijackings**: Four commercial airliners were hijacked by 19 terrorists. The flights involved were American Airlines Flight 11, United Airlines Flight 175, American Airlines Flight 77, and United Airlines Flight 93.\n\n2. **World Trade Center Attacks**: At 8:46 AM, American Airlines Flight 11 crashed into the North Tower of the World Trade Center in New York City. At 9:03 AM, United Airlines Flight 175 struck the South Tower. Both towers eventually collapsed: the South Tower fell at 9:59 AM and the North Tower at 10:28 AM.\n\n3. **Pentagon Attack**: At 9:37 AM, American Airlines Flight 77 crashed into the Pentagon, the headquarters of the U.S. Department of Defense, located in Arlington, Virginia.\n\n4. **Flight 93**: United Airlines Flight 93 was also hijacked, but passengers attempted",
